   "source": [
    "# Beamline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c5929fe4-eb4a-44c4-8a50-1164ef5f5d80",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is an example of plotting lines and surveys.\n",
    "First, create a simple line and a tracker:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "5dcde2bb-196e-4872-a5da-0881e7bfd2f2",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show imports"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "hide-cell",
     "remove-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "import xtrack as xt\n",
    "import xpart as xp\n",
    "import xplt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "xplt.apply_style()\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(36963142)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "2b066eaf-bdc5-490d-b44d-7691a0c1d85c",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "mystnb": {
     "code_prompt_show": "Show line generation code"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "remove-output",
     "hide-cell"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Generate a simple 6-fold symmetric FODO lattice\n",
    "\n",
    "n = 6  # number of sections\n",
    "elements = {\n",
    "    \"QF\": xt.Quadrupole(length=0.3, k1=0.63 / 0.3),\n",
    "    \"QD\": xt.Multipole(length=0.3, knl=[0, -0.48]),\n",
    "    \"MU\": xt.Multipole(length=0.5, knl=[np.pi / n], hxl=[np.pi / n]),\n",
    "}\n",
    "parts = {\n",
    "    \"a\": [\n",
    "        xt.Node(0.7, \"QF\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(1.4, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.1, \"QD\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.8, \"MU\"),\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    \"b\": [\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.2, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(2.9, \"QD\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(3.6, \"MU\"),\n",
    "        xt.Node(4.3, \"QF\"),\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "}\n",
    "nodes = [xt.Node(5.0 * i, \"a\" if i % 2 else \"b\", name=f\"S{i+1}\") for i in range(n)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# sextupoles\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    sx = xt.Multipole(length=0.2, knl=[0, 0, 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (i / n))])\n",
    "    nodes.append(xt.Node(0.2, sx, from_=f\"S{i+1}\", name=f\"S{i+1}SX\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "line = xt.Line.from_sequence(\n",
    "    nodes, length=5.0 * n, sequences=parts, elements=elements, auto_reorder=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "line.particle_ref = xp.Particles()\n",
    "line.build_tracker();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2c25a09a-ce54-4bb5-b3b1-fd0a1a329e8f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Survey"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "44c0af5e-fa7b-4001-b864-92ef59f692ae",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create a survey and a default floor plan plot:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1c3e373e-9fb1-4632-8663-70a4d251cdcd",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "remove-stderr"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ignoring fixed x limits to fulfill fixed data aspect with adjustable data limits.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.FloorPlot(line, labels=[\"S.Q.\", \"S1SX\"])\n",
    "plot.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1968329f",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Customize the plot:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "3187eff8-777c-4cb3-aa0e-e2745095b28d",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": [
     "remove-stderr"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ignoring fixed x limits to fulfill fixed data aspect with adjustable data limits.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot = xplt.FloorPlot(\n",
    "    line.survey(X0=4.5),\n",
    "    projection=\"XZ\",\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    # Adjust box style for element names matching regex\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    # default_boxes=False,  # use this to show *only* the boxes defined below (hiding the default elements)\n",
    "    boxes={\n",
    "        \"S.QF\": dict(color=\"limegreen\"),\n",
    "        \"S.QD\": True,  # default style for defocussing quads\n",
    "        \"S.SX\": dict(width=0.5),\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    # Adjust labels for element names matching regex\n",
    "    #\n",
    "    labels={\n",
    "        \"S.Q.\": True,  # default labels\n",
    "        \"S4MU1\": dict(\n",
    "            text=(\n",
    "                \"A bending magnet\\n\"\n",
    "                \"name: {name}\\n\"\n",
    "                \"l = {element.length} m\\n\"\n",
    "                \"k0l = {element.knl[0]:g} rad\"\n",
    "            ),\n",
    "            xytext=(-3, -4),\n",
    "            bbox={\"fc\": \"white\"},\n",
    "            font=\"monospace\",\n",
    "            c=\"red\",\n",
    "        ),\n",
    "    },\n",
    ")\n",
    "plot.add_scale()\n",
    "plot.legend(loc=\"upper left\")"
   ]
  },

   ]
  },

   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,

     "slide_type": ""

    "tags": [

   },
   "source": [

   ]

   "id": "164e4fdf-0cf0-4dba-8e76-0247e0c74dd0",
